# dcfldd

> Enhanced version of dd for forensics and security
> More information: http://dcfldd.sourceforge.net/

- Copy a disk to a raw image file and hash the image using SHA256:

`dcfldd if=/dev/{any something} of={file something} hash=sha256 hashlog={file something}`

- Copy a disk to a raw image file, hashing each 1 GB chunk:

`dcfldd if=/dev/{any something} of={file something} hash={any something} hashlog={file something} hashwindow={any something}`
